And i see that there is a template file that creates the provider configuration providers.tf.tpl in org setup stage. 


1. We can replace the gcs backend there with

terraform {
  cloud {
    organization = "sp-trial-org"
    workspaces {
      name = "${workspace_name}"
    }
  }
}


2. In /output-files.tf I added this mapping

locals {

  # Add this map to define your custom TFC workspace names
  tfc_workspaces = {
    "0-org-setup"  = "gcp-glz-org-setup-dev"
    "1-vpcsc"      = "gcp-glz-vpcsc-dev"
    "2-networking" = "gcp-glz-network-dev"
    "2-security"   = "gcp-glz-security-dev"
  }


and later on in the provider templates

workspace_name  = lookup(local.tfc_workspaces, each.key, "gcp-glz-${each.key}-dev")
